  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for Linux Kernel Live Patch 17 for SLE 12",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 3.12.60-52_60 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security bugs were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-7308: The packet_set_ring function in net/packet/af_packet.c in the Linux kernel did not properly validate certain block-size data, which allowed local users to cause a denial of service (overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via crafted system calls (bsc#1030575, bsc#1031660).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
